@startuml

' Classes and their attributes
class GameArea {
    name: String
}

class GameElement {
    x: long
    y: long
}

class Shape {
}

class Object {
}

class Opponent {
    lives: int
    +kill()
}

class Boss {
}

' Associations
GameArea "1" -- "1..*" GameElement : has
GameArea "1" -- "1" Boss : knows > 'role name: boss'

GameElement <|-- Shape
GameElement <|-- Object
GameElement <|-- Opponent

Shape "0..*" -- "0..*" Shape : connectsTo 'association name: connectsTo'

Opponent <|-- Boss

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements

- **`GameArea`**: Contains a `name` and is associated with multiple `GameElement`s and exactly one `Boss`.
- **`GameElement`**: Abstract base class with position (`x`, `y`) values.
- **`Shape`**, **`Object`**, **`Opponent`**: Subclasses of `GameElement`.
- **`Shape` to `Shape`**: A self-association to represent that shapes can connect to other shapes (with an association name).
- **`Opponent`**: Has `lives` and a method `kill()`. It is extended by `Boss`.
- **`Boss`**: Exactly one per `GameArea` (with a role name `boss`).

